# Calculate H3K27ac signal on long genes using SAP- adjusted factors (computed in CTCF regions)

# Summary for H3K27ac
## `Linear regression equations fit to data:` --> general formula: *H3K27ac.signal = (\alpha/ * WCE.signal) + Intercept

- 0h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.87326 * WCE.signal) + 6.18404 - 1h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.3435 * WCE.signal) - 0.3084 - 4h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.3865 * WCE.signal) + 4.2390

- 0h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.37916 * WCE.signal) + 2.31610 - 1h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.24840 * WCE.signal) + 2.52123 - 4h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.4106 * WCE.signal) + 1.9113

In [649]:
Count.reads.InBins = function(mark.BAM, regions, spike = 1, binsize = 1, field = "score"){
    
    #Resize each read from BAM to 1bp (center position of each read)
    mark.BAM.res = resize(mark.BAM, width = 1, fix = "center");
    #Compute coverage
    mark.BAM.res = GRanges(coverage(mark.BAM.res, weight="count"));
    mark.BAM.res = makeGRangesBRG(mark.BAM.res[mark.BAM.res$score > 0]);

    #Count DHS signal within each CTCF peak
    mark.BAM.score = getCountsByPositions(mark.BAM.res, regions, binsize = binsize, field="score");
    
    return(mark.BAM.score/spike)
}

# Summary for H3K27ac
## ` Linear regression equations fit to un-normalized data in 5.5kb window centered on CTCF peaks:` --> general formula: *H3K27ac.signal = (\alpha/ * WCE.signal) + Intercept

# center CTCF 40 kb away from marks (in bothe directions), binned in 500bp windows, and 10 Quantiles - 0h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.87326 * WCE.signal) + 6.18404 - 1h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.3435 * WCE.signal) - 0.3084 - 4h Rep1: H3K27ac.signal = (0.3865 * WCE.signal) + 4.2390

- 0h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.37916 * WCE.signal) + 2.31610 - 1h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.24840 * WCE.signal) + 2.52123 - 4h Rep2: H3K27ac.signal = (0.4106 * WCE.signal) + 1.9113

# Compare replicates


Correlations between repliates will be determined by coputing a K-S test and by making scatter plots using data from the same time points in both biological replicates.¶

Good correlation between replicates will be indicated by a D ~ 0 (in the K-S test), and by data points in scatter plot aproaching the x=y diagonal.¶

A violin plot with very similar, if not the same, mean values in both replicates can be an alternative for the scatter plot.¶
